1
00:01:41,439 --> 00:01:41,879
Uncle

2
00:01:43,280 --> 00:01:44,400
We've been walking for three days.

3
00:01:45,719 --> 00:01:47,439
We'll starve before we even get there.

4
00:01:48,760 --> 00:01:49,879
Don't talk like that.

5
00:01:51,120 --> 00:01:52,000
Look at this whole forest.

6
00:01:52,359 --> 00:01:53,359
There's bark and roots everywhere.

7
00:01:53,640 --> 00:01:54,079
We won't starve.

8
00:01:56,239 --> 00:01:57,920
Eating that won't give us any strength.

9
00:01:58,840 --> 00:02:00,079
What if we run into a big animal?

10
00:02:01,719 --> 00:02:02,719
Either it eats us,

11
00:02:03,079 --> 00:02:04,079
or we eat it.

12
00:02:05,840 --> 00:02:06,959
Uncle, you're really fearless.

13
00:02:07,439 --> 00:02:08,080
I need to rest for a bit.

14
00:02:11,280 --> 00:02:11,719
Alright.

15
00:02:12,520 --> 00:02:13,280
It's fine to take a break.

16
00:02:13,560 --> 00:02:14,159
Let's rest.

17
00:02:23,080 --> 00:02:24,039
Old Mountain God

18
00:02:24,199 --> 00:02:25,759
This mountain is split in two.

19
00:02:25,919 --> 00:02:27,280
Everyone digs for their own food.

20
00:02:27,560 --> 00:02:28,800
Everyone fattens up on their own.

21
00:02:29,080 --> 00:02:30,159
But this ginseng

22
00:02:30,719 --> 00:02:32,479
grew right on the border.

23
00:02:32,960 --> 00:02:34,800
We found it first.

24
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:36,840
The ginseng lock is already tied.

25
00:02:37,240 --> 00:02:38,759
It should belong to us.

26
00:02:38,919 --> 00:02:39,360
Exactly.

27
00:02:40,319 --> 00:02:41,520
Who says that's the border?

28
00:02:42,840 --> 00:02:44,800
I say this is our territory.

29
00:02:45,080 --> 00:02:45,560
That's right.

30
00:02:46,439 --> 00:02:47,280
No, Lin the Tall.

31
00:02:50,280 --> 00:02:51,719
If you talk like that,

32
00:02:51,759 --> 00:02:53,039
you're being unreasonable.

33
00:02:53,199 --> 00:02:54,599
What are you gonna do about it?

34
00:02:55,319 --> 00:02:56,919
You want to fight?

35
00:02:57,599 --> 00:02:58,400
You think I'm scared of you?

36
00:02:59,120 --> 00:03:00,360
It's just a few of us.

37
00:03:01,439 --> 00:03:02,639
Don't act tough just because you have more people.

38
00:03:02,639 --> 00:03:04,000
Don't throw your weight around.

39
00:03:05,080 --> 00:03:06,240
Let me tell you,

40
00:03:06,560 --> 00:03:08,800
The Mountain Deity won't stand for this.

41
00:03:08,800 --> 00:03:10,080
Stop wasting time, guys.

42
00:03:10,599 --> 00:03:11,159
Lift the ginseng.

43
00:03:11,240 --> 00:03:12,120
I dare anyone to try.

44
00:03:12,479 --> 00:03:13,560
Watch me.

45
00:03:30,280 --> 00:03:31,520
Lin the Tall

46
00:03:38,080 --> 00:03:39,800
Lin the Tall, you're going too far!

47
00:03:41,599 --> 00:03:42,599
Stop, stop, don't fight!

48
00:03:42,639 --> 00:03:43,120
Alright.

49
00:03:49,319 --> 00:03:50,000
That was too much.

50
00:03:50,240 --> 00:03:50,919
You asked for it.

51
00:03:50,919 --> 00:03:51,439
Stop, stop.

52
00:03:51,680 --> 00:03:52,879
I'll kill you.

53
00:04:01,639 --> 00:04:02,280
Listen to me.

54
00:04:08,840 --> 00:04:09,400
What is it?

55
00:04:10,759 --> 00:04:11,639
Everyone, stop!

56
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:15,199
Our people

57
00:04:15,680 --> 00:04:16,399
Let go too.

58
00:04:24,120 --> 00:04:25,040
This ginseng

59
00:04:25,639 --> 00:04:26,720
I'll decide today.

60
00:04:27,439 --> 00:04:28,519
You can have it.

61
00:04:29,199 --> 00:04:29,560
Foreman

62
00:04:29,560 --> 00:04:30,199
Why give it to him?

63
00:04:30,240 --> 00:04:31,079
Foreman

64
00:04:31,319 --> 00:04:32,120
Shut up.

65
00:04:32,120 --> 00:04:33,160
Why should we let him have it?

66
00:04:41,639 --> 00:04:42,399
Did you hear that?

67
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:45,639
You can't just take it for free.

68
00:04:46,480 --> 00:04:47,759
So, what do you want?

69
00:04:48,639 --> 00:04:49,000
First,

70
00:04:50,680 --> 00:04:52,560
Leave all your money here.

71
00:04:53,560 --> 00:04:54,279
Second,

72
00:04:54,839 --> 00:04:56,279
your food supplies,

73
00:04:57,040 --> 00:04:58,319
leave those too.

74
00:05:00,560 --> 00:05:02,000
Most importantly,

75
00:05:03,319 --> 00:05:04,879
for the next three years,

76
00:05:05,959 --> 00:05:06,959
this territory

77
00:05:06,959 --> 00:05:08,759
belongs to Old Mountain God.

78
00:05:09,160 --> 00:05:11,439
You can't come back here.

79
00:05:11,920 --> 00:05:12,720
Deal?

80
00:05:13,639 --> 00:05:15,040
That's not fair, that's not right.

81
00:05:15,720 --> 00:05:16,560
Enough, enough.

82
00:05:18,439 --> 00:05:18,959
Definitely not.

83
00:05:19,319 --> 00:05:19,879
Fine.

84
00:05:21,319 --> 00:05:21,839
Put it down, put it down.

85
00:05:22,040 --> 00:05:23,079
Money and food,

86
00:05:23,319 --> 00:05:24,000
you can have them.

87
00:05:24,480 --> 00:05:25,160
This place,

88
00:05:25,839 --> 00:05:27,319
I don't care to come back anyway.

89
00:05:30,639 --> 00:05:31,240
Foreman,

90
00:05:31,959 --> 00:05:33,199
Are we just letting them off this easy?

91
00:05:33,920 --> 00:05:35,000
Just this little money and food,

92
00:05:35,040 --> 00:05:35,879
what good is it?

93
00:05:37,319 --> 00:05:38,879
We're here to make money.

94
00:05:39,279 --> 00:05:40,959
Is it worth risking our lives?

95
00:05:44,560 --> 00:05:45,120
Brother,

96
00:05:46,199 --> 00:05:48,120
We just met by chance, thank you.

97
00:05:48,240 --> 00:05:48,839
Don't mention it.

98
00:05:50,240 --> 00:05:51,680
And you, young man,

99
00:05:52,399 --> 00:05:54,800
you're young but skilled.

100
00:05:55,120 --> 00:05:56,079
When you see injustice,

101
00:05:56,319 --> 00:05:57,120
you step in to help.

102
00:05:57,279 --> 00:05:58,079
It's the right thing to do.

103
00:05:58,519 --> 00:05:59,519
Well said.

104
00:06:01,920 --> 00:06:02,600
What's going on?

105
00:06:02,680 --> 00:06:03,240
Gui'er,

106
00:06:05,079 --> 00:06:05,600
I'm starving.

107
00:06:06,079 --> 00:06:06,560
Really starving.

108
00:06:07,319 --> 00:06:08,199
Can you spare some food?

109
00:06:08,800 --> 00:06:10,319
We got lost in these mountains.

110
00:06:10,519 --> 00:06:11,959
Haven't eaten in days.

111
00:06:17,240 --> 00:06:18,439
Time to start work.

112
00:06:19,439 --> 00:06:21,360
The blazing sun shines down on us.

113
00:06:21,680 --> 00:06:22,560
Everyone, get up!

114
00:06:23,519 --> 00:06:25,240
The women in our dreams have grown old.

115
00:06:25,240 --> 00:06:26,000
Is he still okay or not?

116
00:06:26,839 --> 00:06:28,279
He’s fine. Get up and get to work.

117
00:06:29,040 --> 00:06:29,639
No, he’s not.

118
00:06:29,680 --> 00:06:30,560
Are you blind?

119
00:06:31,720 --> 00:06:32,839
Can’t you see what he looks like?

120
00:06:33,040 --> 00:06:33,920
He’s done for, isn’t he?

121
00:06:34,560 --> 00:06:35,560
If he’s useless, drag him out for the dogs.

122
00:06:36,879 --> 00:06:38,079
Just try to move.

123
00:06:41,720 --> 00:06:42,279
Foreman.

124
00:06:42,959 --> 00:06:43,839
My brother is sick.

125
00:06:44,279 --> 00:06:45,480
Can you get him a doctor?

126
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:47,560
Sick, huh?

127
00:06:48,759 --> 00:06:49,920
Can he still eat?

128
00:06:51,600 --> 00:06:52,480
What do you mean?

129
00:06:53,839 --> 00:06:56,439
If he can eat, he can work.

130
00:06:57,199 --> 00:06:57,920
Gold pit.

131
00:06:58,480 --> 00:07:00,000
No freeloaders here.

132
00:07:00,399 --> 00:07:01,360
Please do me a favor.

133
00:07:01,600 --> 00:07:02,560
I’m begging you.

134
00:07:02,920 --> 00:07:03,680
I’ll take him.

135
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:04,519
Is that okay?

136
00:07:06,399 --> 00:07:07,560
Trying to run, huh?

137
00:07:08,759 --> 00:07:10,000
You really have no idea.

138
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:11,959
You think I don’t know who you are?

139
00:07:12,160 --> 00:07:12,720
Get him.

140
00:07:13,879 --> 00:07:15,000
Go all out.

141
00:07:15,439 --> 00:07:15,920
Alright.

142
00:07:16,240 --> 00:07:17,079
So you want to escape?

143
00:07:21,839 --> 00:07:22,319
Brother.

144
00:07:22,800 --> 00:07:23,600
Uncle.

145
00:07:25,680 --> 00:07:26,079
Brother.

146
00:07:27,199 --> 00:07:28,680
Let’s talk this out.

147
00:07:29,040 --> 00:07:29,959
What do you want?

148
00:07:30,079 --> 00:07:31,279
I told you, my brother is sick.

149
00:07:31,639 --> 00:07:32,439
He needs a doctor.

150
00:07:32,800 --> 00:07:34,079
Around here,

151
00:07:34,560 --> 00:07:35,600
no one’s ever heard

152
00:07:35,680 --> 00:07:36,879
of anyone being a doctor.

153
00:07:37,079 --> 00:07:37,680
If there is one,

154
00:07:37,879 --> 00:07:38,959
he’s far away.

155
00:07:39,279 --> 00:07:40,959
Coming here would cost a fortune.

156
00:07:40,959 --> 00:07:41,720
No matter the price,

157
00:07:41,720 --> 00:07:42,680
I’ll pay for it.

158
00:07:42,839 --> 00:07:43,279
Otherwise,

159
00:07:43,639 --> 00:07:44,720
think again.

160
00:07:46,360 --> 00:07:47,399
If someone dies here,

161
00:07:48,199 --> 00:07:49,120
and has family,

162
00:07:49,720 --> 00:07:51,040
we’ll give them some money.

163
00:07:51,160 --> 00:07:52,600
And a plain white coffin.

164
00:07:52,600 --> 00:07:53,279
Forget it.

165
00:07:53,279 --> 00:07:53,720
Brother.

166
00:07:53,720 --> 00:07:54,920
Let’s test it on your nephew today.

167
00:07:54,920 --> 00:07:56,360
Let’s see if there’s really a doctor.

168
00:07:56,759 --> 00:07:57,040
There is.

169
00:07:57,040 --> 00:07:57,560
Uncle.

170
00:07:57,639 --> 00:07:58,319
Yes, yes, yes.

171
00:07:59,319 --> 00:07:59,800
Er, go!

172
00:08:00,759 --> 00:08:01,639
Go find a doctor, quick.

173
00:08:01,800 --> 00:08:02,199
Alright.

174
00:08:02,199 --> 00:08:03,079
Right away, bring him here.

175
00:08:03,759 --> 00:08:05,399
Run yourself, hurry up!

176
00:08:08,480 --> 00:08:09,319
Our team

177
00:08:09,480 --> 00:08:10,800
is getting smaller with every fight.

178
00:08:11,480 --> 00:08:12,800
The Japanese sweep squads

179
00:08:13,480 --> 00:08:14,920
haven’t let up for months.

180
00:08:16,319 --> 00:08:17,240
Our people

181
00:08:17,319 --> 00:08:18,720
are wounded or scattered.

182
00:08:19,480 --> 00:08:20,680
Those who return to us now

183
00:08:21,240 --> 00:08:22,439
and keep fighting the Japanese

184
00:08:22,959 --> 00:08:24,879
are the backbone of the Resistance.

185
00:08:25,160 --> 00:08:25,959
Our lifeblood.

186
00:08:27,399 --> 00:08:28,639
As long as we have our lifeblood,

187
00:08:29,560 --> 00:08:30,759
the flame of resistance

188
00:08:31,240 --> 00:08:32,120
will never die.

189
00:08:33,559 --> 00:08:34,360
Brothers,

190
00:08:35,039 --> 00:08:35,720
Brothers,

191
00:08:36,799 --> 00:08:38,519
no matter how hard it gets, we keep searching.

192
00:08:38,879 --> 00:08:40,000
We gather our sparks

193
00:08:40,639 --> 00:08:41,759
bit by bit,

194
00:08:42,320 --> 00:08:43,080
and bring them all back.

195
00:08:43,320 --> 00:08:43,879
Understand?

196
00:08:44,240 --> 00:08:45,000
Got it, Squad Leader Zhao.

197
00:08:45,399 --> 00:08:45,639
Good.

198
00:08:45,759 --> 00:08:46,080
Let’s go.

199
00:09:03,799 --> 00:09:04,399
Brother,

200
00:09:05,360 --> 00:09:06,240
We meet again.

201
00:09:07,240 --> 00:09:07,519
Yeah.

202
00:09:07,600 --> 00:09:08,480
Nice shooting.

203
00:09:11,679 --> 00:09:13,039
Let me ask you something, brother.

204
00:09:14,080 --> 00:09:15,399
Have you seen anyone in the woods lately?

205
00:09:15,679 --> 00:09:16,519
Run into anyone?

206
00:09:19,679 --> 00:09:20,159
Yeah.

207
00:09:20,480 --> 00:09:21,000
A few.

208
00:09:21,440 --> 00:09:22,000
Just one.

209
00:09:22,399 --> 00:09:23,360
He's a tough guy.

210
00:09:23,879 --> 00:09:25,320
He killed a wolf by himself.

211
00:09:25,840 --> 00:09:26,960
But he's pretty decent.

212
00:09:27,159 --> 00:09:28,279
How can you tell?

213
00:09:29,159 --> 00:09:31,200
He was starving but still shared his food with me.

214
00:09:31,679 --> 00:09:32,519
Where did he go?

215
00:09:33,919 --> 00:09:34,639
Songlin Town.

216
00:09:37,399 --> 00:09:38,039
Songlin Town?

217
00:09:38,360 --> 00:09:39,240
How far is that from here?

218
00:09:42,320 --> 00:09:45,519
Through the woods, it takes at least ten days.

219
00:09:46,759 --> 00:09:47,600
With your leg...

220
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:48,559
It's risky.

221
00:09:50,399 --> 00:09:51,159
In a couple of days,

222
00:09:51,720 --> 00:09:52,679
I'm heading to Songlin Town.

223
00:09:52,840 --> 00:09:53,480
To sell pelts.

224
00:09:54,159 --> 00:09:55,440
We can go together.

225
00:09:56,360 --> 00:09:56,799
As for you,

226
00:09:56,799 --> 00:09:58,399
Take care and heal up.

227
00:09:59,519 --> 00:10:00,159
I can't wait.

228
00:10:02,200 --> 00:10:03,000
I've got urgent business.

229
00:10:03,799 --> 00:10:04,519
Did he say

230
00:10:04,519 --> 00:10:05,600
why he's going to Songlin Town?

231
00:10:06,559 --> 00:10:07,559
No, he didn't.

232
00:10:08,080 --> 00:10:08,639
Brother,

233
00:10:09,480 --> 00:10:10,519
Can I ask you a favor?

234
00:10:11,120 --> 00:10:13,240
If you see a stranger again,

235
00:10:13,879 --> 00:10:14,600
keep him here.

236
00:10:14,720 --> 00:10:15,399
Don't let him leave.

237
00:10:15,720 --> 00:10:16,879
Just say someone's looking for him.

238
00:10:18,039 --> 00:10:18,840
Got it.

239
00:10:19,399 --> 00:10:20,039
Thanks, brother.

240
00:11:22,519 --> 00:11:22,960
Comrade

241
00:11:48,679 --> 00:11:49,360
How are you?

242
00:11:54,639 --> 00:11:55,679
Which unit are you from?

243
00:11:57,720 --> 00:11:58,399
The Fourth Army

244
00:12:01,080 --> 00:12:01,840
From the Fourth Army

245
00:12:42,080 --> 00:12:42,879
Slipped.

246
00:12:44,559 --> 00:12:45,320
Just right.

247
00:12:47,480 --> 00:12:48,159
Let's take a break.

248
00:12:50,840 --> 00:12:51,559
Comrade.

249
00:12:53,039 --> 00:12:53,840
Listen to me.

250
00:12:54,720 --> 00:12:55,799
If we keep this up,

251
00:12:58,480 --> 00:13:00,360
we'll both die in these mountains.

252
00:13:02,240 --> 00:13:03,960
Just make it quick for me.

253
00:13:06,600 --> 00:13:07,279
You go.

254
00:13:11,399 --> 00:13:12,120
No way.

255
00:13:13,399 --> 00:13:14,279
If we go, we go together.

256
00:13:15,840 --> 00:13:16,600
Why?

257
00:13:17,919 --> 00:13:20,080
You want me to fight the Japanese alone?

258
00:13:21,559 --> 00:13:22,639
I have to take you with me.

259
00:13:34,919 --> 00:13:35,639
Comrade.

260
00:13:37,240 --> 00:13:38,240
What's your name?

261
00:13:40,279 --> 00:13:40,960
My name is

262
00:13:43,279 --> 00:13:44,480
Li Ermao.

263
00:13:45,759 --> 00:13:47,080
I'm Tang Deyuan.

264
00:13:55,159 --> 00:13:56,200
Comrade Li Ermao,

265
00:13:58,840 --> 00:14:00,279
if in two days

266
00:14:01,440 --> 00:14:03,000
we still can't get out,

267
00:14:06,080 --> 00:14:07,240
I'll do as you say.

268
00:14:09,000 --> 00:14:09,679
Deal?

269
00:14:12,440 --> 00:14:13,039
Alright.

270
00:14:15,759 --> 00:14:16,279
Okay.

271
00:14:29,120 --> 00:14:29,960
What are you looking at?

272
00:14:31,440 --> 00:14:32,799
Thinking again, huh?

273
00:14:38,440 --> 00:14:39,240
Hey, brother,

274
00:14:39,559 --> 00:14:41,399
could you draw us a map?

275
00:14:41,519 --> 00:14:42,440
Let us

276
00:14:42,759 --> 00:14:44,159
try to find a way out.

277
00:14:45,120 --> 00:14:47,399
Why won't you listen to me?

278
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:48,799
Did you forget how you

279
00:14:48,799 --> 00:14:49,840
ended up meeting me?

280
00:14:49,960 --> 00:14:51,279
Without me leading you,

281
00:14:51,399 --> 00:14:52,919
even if you get out of this valley,

282
00:14:52,960 --> 00:14:54,039
you'll just fall into another trap.

283
00:14:55,919 --> 00:14:58,000
The fighting is fierce right now.

284
00:14:58,639 --> 00:15:00,559
The Japanese are all down the mountain.

285
00:15:00,679 --> 00:15:02,679
All the paths down are blocked.

286
00:15:05,919 --> 00:15:08,200
I won't stop you from fighting the Japanese.

287
00:15:09,360 --> 00:15:10,600
I support you.

288
00:15:11,200 --> 00:15:12,039
But shouldn't you

289
00:15:12,039 --> 00:15:14,039
make sure you survive first?

290
00:15:17,639 --> 00:15:18,480
Come with me.

291
00:15:20,240 --> 00:15:21,480
A little more time won't hurt.

292
00:15:27,080 --> 00:15:27,639
Xiao Gui.

293
00:15:32,320 --> 00:15:32,879
What's wrong?

294
00:15:35,879 --> 00:15:37,480
Didn't you see the snake?

295
00:15:39,039 --> 00:15:39,799
Stop looking.

296
00:15:39,840 --> 00:15:40,720
